[{"location":"#SignalPlots","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots","text":"Documentation for SignalPlots.\n\n","category":"section"},{"location":"#SignalPlots.ResizeableArtist","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots.ResizeableArtist","text":"Base type for resizeable artists, must implement a setdata method and have a baseinfo field\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#SignalPlots.best_scalebar_size","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots.best_scalebar_size","text":"function best_scalebar_size(\n    axis_begin::Real,\n    axis_end::Real,\n    target_frac::AbstractFloat,\n    axis_unit_pow10::Integer = 0;\n    bases = [10, 5, 2, 1],\n    base_penalties = [0, 5, 10, 20],\n    target_frac_penalty = 50\n)\n-> (scalebar_ax_size::Float64, scalebar_units::Int, scalebar_prefix::String)\n\nFinds the best scale bar size for an axis with limits axis_begin and axis_end, where the target scale bar fraction of the axis is target_frac. target_frac must be between 0 and 1. The axis may optionally have units other than natural (e.g. if axis units are uV, then set axis_unit_pow10 = -6).\n\nReturns the size of the scalebar in axis units, scalebar_ax_size, the display size, scalebar_units, as well as the base 10 prefix for the scalebar units, scalebar_prefix, e.g. 'k' for 10^3, 'm' for 10^-3 etc.\n\nRounding is done to match the scalebar to the nearest base specified in bases. Which base is chosen based on base_penalties and target_frac_penalty to minimize target_frac_penalty * abs(frac_at_base - target_frac) + base_penalty. base_penalties and bases must be the same length.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#SignalPlots.downsamp_patch-Union{Tuple{A}, Tuple{A, Vararg{Any}}} where A<:Axis","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots.downsamp_patch","text":"downsamp_patch\n\nPlot a signal as two lines and a fill_between polygon\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SignalPlots.edgefix-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots.edgefix","text":"Adjust the fraction away from 0 and 1, if possible, otherwise return nothing\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SignalPlots.make_dummy_line-Union{Tuple{A}, Tuple{P}, Tuple{A, Vararg{Any}}} where {P<:MPL, A<:Axis{P}}","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots.make_dummy_line","text":"Make a line with place-holder data\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SignalPlots.plot_multi_patch-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{A}, Tuple{P}, Tuple{A, AbstractVector{T}}, Tuple{A, AbstractVector{T}, Vector{A}}} where {P<:SignalPlots.PlotLib, A<:Axis{P}, T<:DynamicTimeseries.AbstractDynamicDownsampler}","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots.plot_multi_patch","text":"plot_multi_patch\n\nPlot a list of DownSampler objects\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SignalPlots.plot_offsets","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots.plot_offsets","text":"plot_offsets(n_line, spacing[, offset = 0])\n\nCalculate the offset for each of n_line number of plots with spacing in between them. Optionally start the first line at offset.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#SignalPlots.plot_spacing-Union{Tuple{A}, Tuple{E}, Tuple{A, Number}} where {E<:Number, A<:AbstractVector{E}}","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots.plot_spacing","text":"plot_spacing(extents[, scale_factor = 1.2])\n\nCalculate the spacing between dataseries for plotting, which is the mean of the extents times an optional scale factor.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SignalPlots.plot_vertical_spacing-Union{Tuple{A}, Tuple{D}, Tuple{E}, Tuple{B}, Tuple{B, A}} where {B<:Axis, E, D<:DynamicTimeseries.AbstractDynamicDownsampler{E}, A<:AbstractVector{D}}","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots.plot_vertical_spacing","text":"plot_vertical_spacing\n\nplot a vector of signals with equal y-spacing between them.\n\nThe spacing between signals is calculated from y-extent of the signals.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SignalPlots.point_boxes-Union{Tuple{P}, Tuple{Axis{P}, Any, Any, Any}, Tuple{Axis{P}, Vararg{Any, 4}}} where P<:SignalPlots.PlotLib","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots.point_boxes","text":"point_boxes\n\nPlot a set of points with boxes around each point, merging if necessary.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SignalPlots.raster_plot","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots.raster_plot","text":"function raster_plot(\n    ax::Py,\n    ticks::AbstractVector{AbstractVector{<:AbstractVector{<:Number}}},\n    pre = 0,\n    post = mapreduce(maximum, max, ticks, init = 0),\n    patch_sets::Union{\n        Nothing,\n        AbstractVector{<:AbstractVector{<:AbstractVector}}\n    } = nothing;\n    tick_plot_args = (:color => \"k\",),\n    patch_plot_args = [(:facecolor => \"#9ecae1\",), (:facecolor => \"#deebf7\",)],\n    top_level::Bool = true\n)\n\nMake a rasterplot for the activity of multiple units, while also displaying the discrete presence of some behavioral information, such as song syllables, for each trial.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#SignalPlots.resizeable_spectrogram","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots.resizeable_spectrogram","text":"resizeable_spectrogram(ax, args...; [listen_ax, toplevel], kwargs...)\n\nplot the spectrogram of a signal in a resizeable context\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#SignalPlots.tonumpy-Tuple{AbstractArray}","page":"Home","title":"SignalPlots.tonumpy","text":"Convert a Julia array to a numpy ndarray for passing to pyqtgraph.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
